<paragraph id="040536E4035A9C3737D940C1A3201F0D" blockId="26.[178,1086,989,1128]" pageId="26" pageNumber="613">
D i a g n o s i s: A broad testaceous fascia, directly in front and contiguous with the posterior bullule, is present in specimens of this species and in those of 
<taxonomicName id="C3BA4D67035A9C3734F540E7A6231F6A" box="[926,1079,1018,1040]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Tarsostenodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="613" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cribripennis">
<emphasis id="36CEEAF6035A9C3734F540E7A6231F6A" box="[926,1079,1018,1040]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="613">T. cribripennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. But, in 
<taxonomicName id="C3BA4D67035A9C3736694704A34A1F48" authorityName="OPITZ" authorityYear="2016" box="[258,350,1048,1069]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Tarsostenodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="613" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vesica">
<emphasis id="36CEEAF6035A9C3736694704A3041F48" box="[258,272,1048,1069]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="613">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="36CEEAF6035A9C3736744704A34A1F48" box="[287,350,1048,1069]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="613">vesica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens the testaceous fascia extends from the epipleural margin to the sutural margin. Also, specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="C3BA4D67035A9C3735094729A0D61F2F" authorityName="OPITZ" authorityYear="2016" box="[610,706,1077,1098]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Tarsostenodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="613" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vesica">
<emphasis id="36CEEAF6035A9C3735094729A0D61F2F" box="[610,706,1077,1098]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="613">T. vesica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are half the length of those of 
<taxonomicName id="C3BA4D67035A9C3733434729A33A1F02" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Tarsostenodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="613" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cribripennis">
<emphasis id="36CEEAF6035A9C3733434729A33A1F02" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="613">T. cribripennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="040536E4035A9C3737D9476BA39F1D65" blockId="26.[178,1086,1143,1536]" pageId="26" pageNumber="613">
D e s c r i p t i o n: Size: Length 4.0 mm; width 1.0 mm. Form: As in 
<figureCitation id="9C812A61035A9C37348D476BA62D1FE8" box="[998,1081,1143,1165]" captionStart="Figs 63-66" captionStartId="37.[178,218,1496,1518]" captionTargetBox="[181,1082,212,1486]" captionTargetId="figure-53@37.[181,1082,212,1486]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="Figs 63-66: Habitus. (63) Tarsostenodes tentus. (64) T. vesica. (65) Tarsostenus antehelvis. (66) T. bicolor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5417192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5417192/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="613">Fig. 64</figureCitation>
. Integument: Forebody dark brown, elytron tricolored, mostly dark brown, with broad testaceous fascia at middle., with 3 white bullules. Head: Cranium coarsely punctate, frons wider than width of eye (FW/EW-30/15); antennal funicular antennomeres subfiliform, 9 
<superScript id="F3CF9BAC035A9C37362B47FEA3581F95" attach="left" box="[320,332,1250,1264]" fontSize="6" pageId="26" pageNumber="613">th</superScript>
and 10 
<superScript id="F3CF9BAC035A9C3736F147FEA3B21F95" attach="left" box="[410,422,1250,1264]" fontSize="6" pageId="26" pageNumber="613">th</superScript>
antennomeres triagonal, 11 
<superScript id="F3CF9BAC035A9C3735AC47FEA0C71F95" attach="left" box="[711,723,1250,1264]" fontSize="6" pageId="26" pageNumber="613">th</superScript>
globose (
<figureCitation id="9C812A61035A9C37345747F5A19E1F9A" box="[828,906,1257,1279]" captionStart="Figs 2-21" captionStartId="7.[178,218,1057,1079]" captionTargetBox="[178,1075,221,1034]" captionTargetId="figure-1@7.[178,1084,212,1048]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs 2-21: Antennae. (2) Paratillus carus. (3) Tarsostenus bicolor. (4) T. kanak. (5) Tarsostenodes tentus. (6) T. guttulus. (7) T. simulator. (8) Tarsostenus univittatus. (9) Tarsostenodes morulus. (10) Blackburniella intricata. (11) Tarsostenodes albonotatus. (12) T. gibbus. (13) T. leucogramma. (14) Tarsostenus antehelvis. (15) Blackburniella apicula. (16) Tarsostenus tricolor. (17) Paratillus atali. (18) Tarsostenodes vesica. (19) T. cribripennis. (20) Tarsostenus hilaris. (21) Tarsostenodes howensis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5417176" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5417176/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="613">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
). Thorax: Pronotum obovate, constricted posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="9C812A61035A9C37355F4619A06B1E79" box="[564,639,1285,1308]" captionStart="Figs 22-40" captionStartId="11.[178,218,1300,1322]" captionTargetBox="[191,1085,239,1289]" captionTargetId="figure-1@11.[178,1085,225,1289]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 22-40: Pronota. (22) Paratillus carus. (23) Tarsostenodes cribripennis. (24) T. guttulus. (25) T. albonotatus. (26) Blackburniella apicula. (27) B. intricata. (28) Tarsostenodes simulator. (29) T. bullatus. (30) T. tentus. (31) T. gibbus. (32) T. leucogramma. (33) T. howensis. (34) T. vesica. (35) Tarsostenus hilaris. (36) Tarsostenus. univittatus. (37) T. morulus. (38) T. bicolor. (39) T. kanak. (40) Paratillus atali." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5417178" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5417178/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="613">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
) (
<collectionCode id="62ABAE21035A9C3735FD461AA0A01E7E" box="[662,692,1286,1307]" country="Czech Republic" name="Západoceské muzeum v Plzni" pageId="26" pageNumber="613" type="Museum">PL</collectionCode>
/PW- 71/63), coarsely punctated, with a longitudinal glabrous plate, without tubercle at sides; elytral disc with prominent subbasal umbo, with epipleural, sutural, and posterior bullules, with large asetiferous punctations that extend to the elytral apex (
<collectionCode id="62ABAE21035A9C3735554647A04B1E14" box="[574,607,1371,1393]" pageId="26" pageNumber="613">EL</collectionCode>
/EW-160/30); disc constricted and compressed at middle. Abdomen: Male pygidium not incised at middle of anterior margin; phallobase extended anteriorly ventrally, lobes particularly short, fimbriate, delineated basally by a faint transverse sclerotic line, phallobasic rod extended laterally, phallobasic struts contiguous with phallobasic apodeme, phallic apex broad triagonal, apex curvate, phallic plates wide (
<figureCitation id="9C812A61035A9C37365846F6A36B1D65" box="[307,383,1514,1536]" captionStart="Figs 83-88" captionStartId="40.[178,218,790,812]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,212,773]" captionTargetId="figure-66@40.[178,1085,212,773]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="Figs 83-88: Male terminalia. (83) Tarsostenodes tentus. (84) T. vesica. (85) Tarsostenus antehelvis. (86) T. bicolor. (87) T. hilaris. (88) T. univittatus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5417198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5417198/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="613">Fig. 84</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="040536E4035A9C3737D94513A0951D27" blockId="26.[178,1085,1551,1602]" pageId="26" pageNumber="613">
V a r i a t i o n: Size: Length 3.0-4.0 mm; width 0.8-1.0 mm. Other than size, the 
<specimenCount id="12BCFD6D035A9C37337C4513A3081D27" pageId="26" pageNumber="613" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
before me are quite homogeneous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="040536E4035B9C3637D943C7A1EF1B94" blockId="27.[178,1019,219,241]" box="[178,1019,219,241]" pageId="27" pageNumber="614">N a t u r a l H i s t o r y: The available specimens were collected in November.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="040536E4035B9C3637D9421DA63D1A73" blockId="27.[178,1065,256,278]" box="[178,1065,256,278]" pageId="27" pageNumber="614">
D i s t r i b u t i o n (
<figureCitation id="9C812A61035B9C3636F1421CA3F21A73" box="[410,486,256,278]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="43.[178,211,1295,1317]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,211,1284]" captionTargetId="figure-1@43.[178,1085,211,1285]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="Fig. 91: Geographic distribution of species as noted." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5417204" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5417204/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="614">Fig. 91</figureCitation>
