<paragraph id="040536E4035B9C3637D9423AA0F31A3C" blockId="27.[178,1085,293,345]" pageId="27" pageNumber="614">
E t y m o l o g y: The specific epithet 
<emphasis id="36CEEAF6035B9C363531423AA08D1A5E" box="[602,665,294,315]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="614">vesica</emphasis>
(= blister) is a Latin noun. The name refers to the well-developed bullules on the elytral disc.
